Download State Boundaries

(We may choose to use the data to set a bounding box instead but for now we can set states)

USAb <- geoboundaries(c("United States"), "adm1")

states<- USAb%>%
  filter(shapeName %in%  c('Florida', 'Virginia', 'Georgia', 'North Carolina', 'Texas'))

Use the Boundaries to get elevation data from USGS

(for now use a big resolution, we can experiment with smaller OR we can consider using a point extraction for analysis and then a high resolution surface for prediction)

Then we plot the map and boundaries

(we need to consider that the raster library is being discontinued, and terra will be the proper one also should use TMaps for interactivity)

output_tiles <- get_tiles(states,
                          services = c("elevation", "ortho"),
                          resolution = 3000 # pixel side length in meters
)

plot(raster(output_tiles[["elevation"]][[1]]))
plot(st_geometry(states), add=TRUE)
